Package: robisdb
Title: Fast Access to OBIS Data via DuckDB and Parquet
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Silas", "Principe", , "silasprincipe5@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Query OBIS (Ocean Biodiversity Information System) open data and
    derived products directly with DuckDB against their public Parquet
    snapshots, instead of paging through the OBIS API. Provides drop-in
    equivalents of key 'robis' functions ('occurrence()', 'checklist()',
    'measurements()'), a lightweight dplyr-style query builder for the parts
    of the schema those functions don't cover, and helpers for spatial and H3
    hexagonal-indexing operations. Generally much faster than the API for
    bulk downloads, nut you need a local (or S3-streamed) copy of
    the dataset.
